Mohamud is the first man to win back the presidency after being voted out of office, but he faces a daunting in-tray at the start of his second term: Somalia has been crippled by years of Islamist insurgency and is currently being ravaged by a severe drought. But his election in a vote delayed by over a year means a $400 million aid package from the International Monetary Fund now won't automatically expire this month. --BBC--